# VectoCart Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# ============================================
# Supabase Configuration (Required)
# ============================================
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard:
# https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api

# Preferred: Use VITE_ prefix (WXT supports Vite-style env vars)
WXT_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
WXT_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key-here

# Alternative: Use WXT_ prefix (WXT-specific naming)
# WXT_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
# WXT_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key-here

# Note: The code will use VITE_* if available, otherwise fall back to WXT_*
# You only need to set one set (either VITE_* or WXT_*), not both

# ============================================
# Google OAuth Configuration (Required)
# ============================================
# Get this from Google Cloud Console:
# https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials

# Create an OAuth 2.0 Client ID for "Chrome Extension" application type
# The authorized redirect URI will be: https://\<extension-id\>.chromiumapp.org
# (WXT will automatically use your extension ID)
WXT_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ============================================
# Build Mode (Optional - Auto-detected by WXT)
# ============================================
# WXT automatically sets MODE based on command:
# - "pnpm dev" → MODE=development (import.meta.env.DEV = true)
# - "pnpm build" → MODE=production (import.meta.env.PROD = true)
#
# You can override MODE if needed (e.g., for staging):
# MODE=development
# or
# MODE=production
#
# Note: This is usually not needed as WXT sets it automatically.
# The logger uses import.meta.env.DEV to determine if logs should be shown.

# ============================================
# How to Get These Values
# ============================================

# 1. Supabase URL and Anon Key:
#    - Go to https://app.supabase.com
#    - Select your project (or create one)
#    - Go to Settings > API
#    - Copy "Project URL" → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - Copy "anon public" key → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

# 2. Google OAuth Client ID:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
#    - Create a new project or select existing
#    - Enable Google+ API
#    - Go to APIs & Services > Credentials
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
#    - Application type: "Chrome Extension"
#    - Copy the Client ID → WXT_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID

# ============================================
# Security Notes
# ============================================
# - The Supabase anon key is safe to expose in client code (it's public)
#   Security is enforced via Row Level Security (RLS) policies in Supabase
# - The Google OAuth client ID is also public (security via OAuth flow)
# - Never commit .env file to git (already in .gitignore)
# - Never expose service role keys or secrets in client code

# ============================================
# WXT Environment Variable Notes
# ============================================
# - WXT uses Vite under the hood, so VITE_* prefix works
# - WXT also supports WXT_* prefix for WXT-specific variables
# - All environment variables are accessible via import.meta.env.*
# - MODE is automatically set by WXT based on dev/build commands
